The councillor has been arrested in connection with a shooting in which three people were wounded. CAPE TOWN - A Beaufort West African National Congress (ANC) councillor has been arrested in connection with a shooting in which three people were wounded.The shooting occurred at the weekend. The police's Malcolm Pojie says the motive is unclear. An attempted murder case has been opened against a 55-year-old man. We confiscated a 9mm pistol for forensic tests. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)